# SSBM Nucleus Desktop

install and manage your melee mods

## features

- organize your skin collection
- auto-generate missing CSPs from DATs
- 1-click installation
- batch import dozens of mods at once
- slippi-safe costume validation
- easily backup or share with friends

## download

get the latest release from the [releases page](../../releases)

## credits

built with [MexManager](https://github.com/Ploaj/MexManager) and [HSDRawViewer](https://github.com/Ploaj/HSDLib) by Ploaj


GUIDE:
SSBM NUCLEUS

SSBM Nucleus consists of 2 programs: 

- the website, [ssbmnucleus.net](http://ssbmnucleus.net),   
- and the desktop app (download at [https://github.com/davidfeira/meleeNexus/releases/tag/v1.0](https://github.com/davidfeira/meleeNexus/releases/tag/v1.0)) 

FEATURES:  
	*Website:*

- Upload and download mods  
- Special integration with the desktop app to make mod installation super user friendly

	*App:*

- Store mods and their associated assets in an organized and visual way  
- Automatic CSP asset generation for character mods   
- Automatic validation of costumes for netplay safety (using [Costume Validator](https://ssbmtextures.com/other-mod-types/costume-validator-by-ploaj/) by Ploaj)  
- Batch install dozens of mods at once (Built on top of the MEX system and Dynamic Alternate Stages by Unclepunch, up to 256 skins for each character and stage, without removing the originals)    
- Easily downscale CSPs to manage the memory constraints on Dolphin/Console

		  
		PLANNED SOON:

- Automatic texture pack creation for dolphin for CSPs (no more blurry textures or CSP memory constraints on dolphin)  
- Automatic stock asset creation  
- Automatic stage safety validation (hopefully)  
- Custom stage storage/installation support, right now we only support skins for the legal stages


HOW TO USE IT:

1\. [Download and install the desktop app](https://github.com/davidfeira/meleeNexus/releases/tag/v1.0)![][image1]  
Windows might complain that it's a virus, click run anyway then continue through the installer. (Feel free to check the open source code on github, trust me bro its not a virus)  
	![][image2]

1. Install .net Core Runtime, or else the program will think every skin is not safe for netplay   
   2. Installation complete\!

	  
2\. Get skins into your vault, there are several methods

1. *Recommended: [ssbmnucleus.net](http://ssbmnucleus.net)*

   Go to the website, and find a skin that you want, then scroll down to the bottom of the post and find the “Add to Nucleus” button

   ![][image3]

   	Make sure your desktop app is open, then click the button. A browser popup will  show up  asking if you'd like to open the link with SSBM Nucleus,  click Open Link

   If it worked you should see a popup like this on your desktop app, and the skin  should appear in your vault:

   Done\! Add as many as you want\!

   

2. *Import button*

   If you have a skin that is not on the website that you'd like to add to your vault, you can use the Import file button on the homepage

			![][image4]

Just put the skin .dat, csp image, and stock image into a zip file and import the ZIP. For stages, just the .dat and a screenshot. 

\[IMAGE COMING SOON\]

This works perfectly with skins already in other Mex based builds, simply export the costume as a zip using mex-tool and it will be perfectly formatted for import.

\[IMAGE COMING SOON\]

 If you are missing a CSP, the program will automatically generate one for you. If you are missing a stock icon, it will copy over a vanilla stock as a placeholder. 

\[IMAGE COMING SOON\]

You can also edit the assets if they didn't import properly, or if you get better ones later

*3\. Installation:*  
	Once you have all the mods you want downloaded, time to install, click the MEX Manager tab at the top right, then click Create from Vanilla ISO and locate your melee iso, after you click your iso it will then ask you where to save your project folder for the new modded build:  
![][image5]  
It can take a minute or two, once its done it will open a menu like this.   
![][image6]  
For each character it shows the skins currently in the build on the left and all the skins in your vault on the right. To import a skin, simply make sure its checkbox is selected, then click import all selected.   
*![][image7]*  
It should then appear on the left (sometimes you need to click refresh or click back and forth to a different character, it's still a bit buggy), meaning it's installed\!  
![][image8]

You can select as many mods as you want to import at once, even across different characters (you could import 8 falco skins, 5 fox skins, and 4 marth skins all at the same time for example). I tested with 600 mods across almost every character and it worked fine so I don't think there's any limit. 

*4\. Exporting the .iso*  
*![][image9]*  
Once you have all the character and stage mods you want installed, click the export iso button in the top left, it will open a menu like this:

CSP compression automatically compresses the CSPs to a smaller size to save memory. 1 means they are full resolution, while 0.50 would mean they are compressed to half size. This feature exists because if you have too many CSPs, melee will crash from running out of memory on the character select screen. So when we add more csps, we need to make them all smaller to compensate.

Basically all this means:  
The more mods you have, the more you will need to turn down this value. If you launch your iso and your game crashes on the css, you probably just need to turn down this value to save some memory.  

Just ignore the Color Smash checkbox.

Once the value is set, click Start Export, wait a moment, then click download game and save it with your other isos.

Open the iso with Dolphin and enjoy\!\!

![][image10]
